      <scopecontent id="aspace_c7ed03b99a077a9318aa7275fd66e8f2">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>The Paul Stephen Galatowitsch papers consist of research files documenting AIDS and AIDS response in New Haven in the 1980s and 1990s. Material includes subject files, interview transcripts, reports related to local AIDS public policy and interventions, papers and presentations, and news clippings and research bibliographies compiled or written by Galatowitsch for his 1996 Yale dissertation, "An Institutional, Organizational, and Cultural Analysis of New Haven, Connecticut's Response to the AIDS Epidemic, 1980-1991."</p>  
      </scopecontent>
  
  
  
  
  
